b'You\xe2\x80\x99ve probably heard of inflation, but do you know how it affects your purchasing power?

Inflation is the rate at which the price of goods and services in an economy increases over a period of time. When prices rise, your money buys less.

The erosion of purchasing power is the most familiar problem. Commonly-purchased household goods become more expensive, and so a single unit of currency loses value as it buys fewer goods and services.

For example, $100 in 1968 was only worth $14.02 in purchasing power in 2018. For a forward-looking example, if a cup of coffee costs $2 today, and the annual inflation rate was 5%, in 30 years that same cup of coffee would cost $8.64!

As an investor, you should be aware of inflation. If you earn less than the rate of inflation on your investments, you would face reduced purchasing power when your investments are converted into cash. The good news is, with a sound investment strategy you can guard against inflation and help maintain your purchasing power and standard of living in retirement. 

See the @scotiabank link in bio to read the full article.

#FLM2020 #FinancialLiteracy #finlit #money #finance'

b'Curious about TFSAs?

A TFSA, or Tax-Free savings Account, is a registered account in which the income you earn is completely tax-free \xe2\x80\x93 even when you withdraw your funds.

It\xe2\x80\x99s a great way to start saving for anyone, and is flexible if something comes up and you need to withdraw funds early. It works for short-term and long-term goals, from saving for a vacation to buying a car and even retirement.

A TFSA is like an umbrella, and within the account you can have a bunch of different investments like GICs, mutual funds, savings and more. It all depends on your risk tolerance and personal goals.

For more info on TFSAs and how to use them, click the @scotiabank link in bio to learn more.'

b'What\xe2\x80\x99s the difference between an RRSP and a TFSA?

An RRSP is a Registered Retirement Savings Plan. It\xe2\x80\x99s an account intended to help you save for retirement, and contributions made result in immediate income tax deductions in the year you contribute.  One of the main benefits of an RRSP is that you defer paying taxes on the money you put in today and any investment income earned, until you withdraw your money in retirement. 

A TFSA, or Tax-Free Savings Account, can be used to save towards many different goals, because you\xe2\x80\x99re free to withdraw at any time without penalties. The main benefit of a TFSA is that it is completely tax free. Since you\xe2\x80\x99ve already been taxed on the money you put into your TFSA, any income you earn from the investments within it are completely tax free, even when you withdraw from it.

For more tips on RRSPs, TFSAs and how they could work for you, visit the @scotiabank link in bio.'

b':repeat_button: Repost @terryfoxfoundation #OnThisDay - September 1, 1980 - near Thunder Bay, ON
 
As he neared the 18 mile mark, Terry could see miles of supporters along the highway, cheering him on, saying, \xe2\x80\x9cKeep going, you can do it, we\xe2\x80\x99re all behind you.\xe2\x80\x9d Terry felt like he was having a heart attack, the pain was so intense. He took a break and crawled into his sleeping bag, hoping the pain might subside. It didn\xe2\x80\x99t. Terry got back up, ran another mile until he could see no more people along the road. It was then he said to himself, \xe2\x80\x9cThis may be my last mile.\xe2\x80\x9d He got in the van and asked his best friend Doug to take him to a hospital. Later that day, Terry called his parents in Port Coquitlam and told them the cancer had returned. He had run his last mile of the Marathon of Hope.
 
In his last journal entry, all Terry wrote was: "21 miles. 3,339 miles total."
 
Honour Terry's Try. Donate today. terryfox.org/donate/
***
@scotiabank: 
Today marks forty years since Terry Fox was forced to stop his Marathon of Hope. Scotiabank is honoured to support Terry Fox PROFYLE, a program that brings new hope to young people with rare and hard-to-treat cancers. Visit TerryFox.org/run to register for the Virtual Terry Fox Run. #TrylikeTerry'

b":repeat_button: #Repost @stepstonesfy August\xe2\x80\x99s Mentor of the Month is brought to us by @Scotiabank! \xe2\x80\x89
\xe2\x80\x89
Scotiabank\xe2\x80\x99s generous funding of our Youth Support Services program gives youth like Leah the opportunity to connect with incredible mentors like Colleen! Who better to honour Colleen than Leah herself:\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x80\x89
\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x80\x89
\xe2\x80\x9cYou can try to build a bond for 4 years and it can go nowhere, but sometimes you can build a bond in 4 months with someone and it means everything. From the time I met Colleen, we both felt the connection. Colleen has been great to me and to my son, Zye, and I am truly blessed and grateful to have a person in my life to see me at my worst and help me to become my best again. With her help over the past 4 months, I was able to smile a little more and cry a lot less. Zye was able to accomplish more of his development skills in a comfortable home with someone he truly loves and looks up to. We do karaoke most Friday nights together or we just bond with each other by sharing things or going places I've never been. I was stuck for a very long time and now I am not, I am safe! Thank you for bringing the light to my tunnel and helping me become the person I am becoming. Looking forward to more with you and the memories we shall continue to have!\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x80\x89
\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x80\x89
Thank you to Leah for her beautifully written tribute, thank you to our partners @nevertoolate.on for helping connect these two, and thank you to Scotiabank for your continued support of youth at StepStones. Congratulations Colleen!\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x80\x89
\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x80\x89
#mentorofthemonth #mentorship"
